item.dc:creator: @Jordyboy Jordyboy
item.description:
@Jordyboy wrote:

you dont have to port forward on the vps
its pretty straight forward if you know how to set up FTP server and Java.
the domain is just a subdomain so, http://example.vpscustomer.com or something.
And you have root access over the VPS.
if u need help with that drop me a pm ill be sure to help.
also lite one won’t do for rsps, thats for webhosting, i suggest the one after or second one after.
